AN/AX Docs L10N (help files)
	•	Export translated dita files from XTM
	•	Set the language for each dita file from “en-us” to the translated language. You just need to use Notepad++, or whatever,  to replace xml:lang=”en-us” with xml:lang=”zh-cn”. Make sure the total number of replacements matches the number of files for the language.

PT - xml:lang=”pt”
FR - xml:lang=”fr”
ES - xml:lang=”es”
DE - xml:lang=”de”
ZH - xml:lang=”zh-cn”
KO - xml:lang=”ko-kr”
PL - xml:lang=”pl”
JA - xml:lang=”ja-jp”

	•	Copy the ditamaps from the dita\AuditExchange R4 (or latest EN release) folder to the NL\AuditExchange R4 (or latest L10N release) folder. You’ll need to set the appropriate language and substitute the translated title of the guide. You can use the translated title from the corresponding home.dita file or get the translations from TM.

	•	Common\feedback.html is not used anymore!

	•	Check for English terms in localized dita files.
English-language comments and user-created strings in ACLScript examples should be translated. They’ll be completely meaningless to non-English users if they’re not. Unlike the ACLScript keywords, the comments do not need to remain in English.

